From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Christian Walter <christian.walter@9elements.com>
Date: Tue, 15 Apr 2026 15:30:00 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] usb: gadget: gxp-udc: add port watchdog for EHCI handoff

The GXP SoC's Virtual USB Hub Controller (VUHC) does not generate a
PORTEN_CHANGE interrupt to the UDC when the host EHCI controller
changes ownership from BIOS to OS. The port silently transitions
from enabled to disabled without any notification to the UDC driver.

After the initial enumeration by BIOS, the connect-retry worker
sees PORTENABLESTS=1 and exits permanently. When the OS takes over
EHCI and the port goes disabled, the UDC is left with a stale
device address and no mechanism to re-present itself.

Fix this by converting the connect-retry worker from one-shot to a
watchdog: after successful enumeration, instead of exiting, continue
polling EVDCS at a reduced rate (GXP_UDC_WATCHDOG_MS, default 10s).
If the watchdog detects the port went disabled while CONNECT is
still asserted, it resets connect_retries to 0 and falls through to
the existing full disconnect/connect retry cycle.

This matches the intent of HPE's userspace udc-reconnect.sh (which
polls the VUHC port_owner GPIO at 100ms and does a soft_connect
toggle), but is handled entirely in the kernel driver at a sensible
polling rate.

Signed-off-by: Christian Walter <christian.walter@9elements.com>
---
 drivers/usb/gadget/udc/gxp_udc.c | 12 +++++++++++-
 1 file changed, 11 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/drivers/usb/gadget/udc/gxp_udc.c b/drivers/usb/gadget/udc/gxp_udc.c
index 4b3c1e7f8a01..e9f2d3a1b5c0 100644
--- a/drivers/usb/gadget/udc/gxp_udc.c
+++ b/drivers/usb/gadget/udc/gxp_udc.c
@@ -134,6 +134,7 @@ static bool udcg_init_done;
 #define GXP_UDC_CONNECT_RETRY_MS	5000
 #define GXP_UDC_CONNECT_MAX_RETRIES	24
 #define GXP_UDC_IRQ_MAX_ITERATIONS	100
+#define GXP_UDC_WATCHDOG_MS		10000
 
 static DEFINE_MUTEX(udcg_init_mutex);
 static bool udcg_init_done;
@@ -654,7 +655,13 @@ static void gxp_udc_connect_retry_work(struct work_struct *work)
 	evdcs = readl(drvdata->base + EVDCS);
 	if (evdcs & EVDCS_PORTENABLESTS) {
-		/* Port is enabled, host enumerated us — done */
+		/* Port is enabled -- stay alive as watchdog to
+		 * detect EHCI handoff (VUHC does not generate
+		 * PORTEN_CHANGE on port ownership changes).
+		 */
+		drvdata->connect_retries = 0;
 		spin_unlock_irqrestore(&drvdata->lock, flags);
+		schedule_delayed_work(&drvdata->connect_work,
+				      msecs_to_jiffies(GXP_UDC_WATCHDOG_MS));
 		return;
 	}
 
@@ -672,6 +679,9 @@ static void gxp_udc_connect_retry_work(struct work_struct *work)
 		return;
 	}
 
+	if (drvdata->connect_retries == 0)
+		dev_info(&drvdata->pdev->dev,
+			 "port disabled, restarting enumeration\n");
 	drvdata->connect_retries++;
 	dev_dbg(&drvdata->pdev->dev,
 		"vdev%d: connect retry %d/%d\n",
-- 
2.48.1
